article.headline: Old Dominion 72, Virginia Tech 69
article.story: NORFOLK, Va. (AP) -- Brandon Johnson scored 15 and Abdi Lidonde added 12 to earn Old Dominion a last minute victory over Virginia Tech, 72-69 Sunday. Old Dominion (6-4) took control early in the game, aided by a pair of 3-pointers by Lidonde and Brian Henderson. A.D. Vassallo added 12 of his 20 points to help bring Virginia Tech (5-4) to within four. But Jonathan Adams added three and the Monarchs went into half time leading 45-33. Malcom Delaney added 10 in the second half to help the Hokies closed the gap. A 3-pointer from Vassallo with 26 seconds on the clock pulled Virginia Tech to within one shot of the win. But Johnson landed a free-throw and the Monarchs handed the Hokies a loss. Delaney had 17 points for Virginia Tech.
